    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Jackson Merrill** (66.12) and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (61.04) serving as our offensive anchors. **Jackson Merrill** benefits significantly from a favorable platoon matchup against right-hander Luis Castillo, capitalizing on his elevated position in the three-hole to maximize run production. Meanwhile, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** maintains a high floor due to his elite xwOBA (.384) despite a neutral matchup, providing essential stability in the heart of our order. While **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (59.95) narrowly missed the \"Strong\" threshold of 60, he remains a high-upside play due to a dynamic platoon advantage against Ashcraft, making him a critical component of our pursuit of league-leading counting stats today.\n\nThe most difficult benching decision of the day involved **Brady House**, who graded out at 47.22. While **Brady House** possesses the raw power profile we prioritize, his score was suppressed by the high SB-prevention rate of opposing pitcher Ashcraft, which complicates the stolen base potential we desperately need to chase in our 5x5 format. Consequently, we opted for the higher projected efficiency of **Jacob Wilson** (57.74), whose matchup against the slightly more hittable Leiter outweighs the upside **Brady House** would provide in a vacuum. We continue to monitor the status of **Gunnar Henderson**, whose score (47.79) remains surprisingly modest today due to a negative platoon split against Messick; however, his elite talent profile dictates he remains in the lineup to avoid missing a potential multi-HR day. \n\nLooking ahead, we are tracking the weather closely for all matchups, though no major atmospheric risks are currently flagged for our core starters. We remain cautious of **Miguel Vargas** (50.05) and **Josh Jung** (53.08); while both are starting, their scores reflect the difficulty of facing Matz and Lopez respectively. Should the game environment shift or lineups be adjusted prior to first pitch, we are prepared to shift leverage toward our bench depth, particularly if we need to pinch-hit for speed or high-average contact to protect our category standings.",
